content:
Create a Catalog Category

A catalog category represents groups of catalog items in Service Catalog. Organizing catalog items under a catalog category makes those catalog items viewable in Aura.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions

You can organize categories under a primary category. In Service Catalog, you can create up to 200 categories: 100 primary categories and 100 secondary categories.

From Setup, enter Service Catalog, select Catalog Settings.
On the Catalog Categorization Method dropdown, select Catalog Categories.
Click Categories Builder.
To create a catalog category, click New Catalog Category.
Enter a name, select a parent category (if applicable), and upload an optional image.
A category can have only one parent category; you can’t nest parent categories.

When a category is created, it’s always visible in Service Catalog. A category is visible in the Service Cloud Community only when it’s active and at least one item is visible to the user.

You can edit and delete created catalog categories. You can delete a catalog category if it has no assigned catalog items. When all items are removed, a category can be deprecated and hidden from the UI, but still available for reporting.
title: Service Catalog Category Creation
